Package: cvar
Type: Package
Title: Compute Conditional Value-at-Risk and Value-at-Risk
Version: 0.1-0
Date: 2018-04-07
Author: Georgi N. Boshnakov
Maintainer: Georgi N. Boshnakov <georgi.boshnakov@manchester.ac.uk>
Description: Compute Conditional Value-at-Risk (CVaR) and
     Value-at-Risk (VaR) from a quantile function, distribution
     function, random number generator or probability dnsity function.
     CVaR is also known as Expected shortfall. Virtually any
     continuous distribution can be specified.  The functions are
     vectorised over the arguments.
Imports: stats, utils, gbutils, Rdpack (>= 0.7)
RdMacros: Rdpack
License: GPL (>=2)
Collate: VaR.R cvar-package.R
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Suggests: testthat, PerformanceAnalytics
